The paper deals with the problem of access-balancing in distributed storage systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), distributed systems (cs.DS), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new combinatorial model and uses graph theory concepts, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper provides results for optimization problems, which are relevant to optimization and control (cs.SI).
